    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential memory management issues in free_cu_to_du_rrc_info function\n\n### Summary\nThe `free_cu_to_du_rrc_info` function in f1ap_ue_context.c was using a macro-based approach for memory deallocation that could lead to undefined behavior in certain edge cases. This change replaces the macro calls with explicit memory management to improve robustness.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_ue_context.c`: Replaced FREE_OPT_BYTE_ARRAY macro calls with explicit NULL checks and memory deallocation logic in the free_cu_to_du_rrc_info function. Added NULL assignment after freeing to prevent dangling pointers.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling free_cu_to_du_rrc_info() during UE context modification procedures, users may experience unexpected behavior including potential memory corruption or crashes under certain load conditions. The issue manifests as intermittent failures during F1AP message processing, particularly when handling CU-to-DU RRC information transfer.\n\n"
}